{"tid":2372421,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"「真撤資」對沖基金Elliott Management 撤出香港","createTime":"2021-01-19T15:34:26.000Z","updateTime":"2021-01-19T15:47:00.000Z","uid":182007,"like":8,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":8,"replies":[{"pid":"eb8c4efbd61ce890147be32570d5155013974fad","tid":2372421,"uid":182007,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-19T15:34:26.000Z","msg":"<span class=\"large\"><strong><span class=\"red\">US hedge fund Elliott Management is closing its Hong Kong office</span></strong></span>, becoming one of the first large financial institutions to shutter operations in the territory since it entered a period of civil unrest and political tension in 2019.<br />\n<br />\nThe activist fund, which was founded in 1977 by billionaire Paul Singer and has launched dozens of campaigns globally, has had a presence in Hong Kong for 15 years. It will move staff based in Hong Kong to its offices in London and Tokyo, which will become its only base in Asia.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.ft.com/content/f47107f8-8f9e-4a42-85d4-52c4b3707a13\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff47107f8-8f9e-4a42-85d4-52c4b3707a13&d=CthjHxCXz%2Bl0vOF3eBkmesjT01h1KCp2%2Bw2KB0oDRGE%3D&h=af342159\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ft.com/content/f47107f8-8f9e-4a42-85d4-52c4b3707a13</a>"},{"pid":"644574a5f1e1e689868f64f4b85e56361328a43a","tid":2372421,"uid":19454,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-19T15:35:19.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/24.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/24.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/24.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/24.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/24.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c5da53075882cd96bfcf3487d339277bd581389f","tid":2372421,"uid":33408,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-19T15:36:30.000Z","msg":"沒事兒 咱們有北水<img s